what_worked: Applied date_cte_isolate, multi_dimension_prefetch: Applied novel_structural_decomposition by creating independent CTEs for each dimension with their filters, then joining them to the fact table in a final CTE before computing the MIN() aggregations. This allows PostgreSQL to optimize each dimension filter independently and use efficient hash joins.
why_it_worked: Pre-filtering date dimension into CTE reduces hash join probe table from 73K to ~365 rows; Pre-filtering multiple dimension tables in parallel reduces join fan-out
